sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM daily_updates 
WHERE new_cases > 0;

SELECT age_group, AVG(pos_test_rate) AS average_positivity_rate
FROM testing_data
GROUP BY age_group;

external_knowledge:
- "storm of at least 5 new cases" refers to an average number of new cases greater than 5;
- "positivity rate above 5%" refers to an average positivity rate greater than 0.05;
- "month of July 2020" is the date range from '2020-07-01' to '2020-07-31'.

- "the shadow of death looms largest" refers to the highest death percentages;
- "souls departed" refers to the total number of deaths;
- "living population" refers to the total population of the county.

- "a significant number of people tested" refers to a high number of individuals tested in the county;
- "percentage of those who tested positive is more than a whisper (5%)" means the positivity rate is greater than 5%;
- "number of those who have returned to health (recovered) is more than a handful (50)" means the total number of recovered individuals is greater than 50.

- The positivity rate is calculated as the number of positive cases divided by the total number of tests;
- "Average positivity rate exceeding 5%" implies a higher than average risk of infection;
- "More than 1000 individuals tested" ensures a significant sample size for statistical relevance.

- 'Significant number' refers to more than 10 new cases and more than 50 individuals recovered;
- 'Younger adult population' refers to the age group '18-45';
- 'Higher positivity rate' means the positivity rate is greater than 0.05.
